        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 10 at 11:10PM CDT until August 11 at 12:15AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
South central Dallam County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Central Hartley County in the Panhandle of Texas...

* Until 1215 AM CDT.

* At 1110 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 5 miles northeast
of Romero, or 17 miles southeast of Amistad, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.

* Locations impacted include...
Romero.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
